Now we can see why #bitcoin is unique, and the mysterious founding and initial ethical distribution are essential to its decentralization.

Other cryptos are just securities, similar to stocks, centralized and managed by a team.

Bitcoin is a protocol run by the people.

There was no such thing for #bitcoin.

Bitcoin has always been mined not issued.

The hype around bitcoin was so low that bitcoin was exchanged without a defined price for about two years.

Reason #2: Coin Issuance/Distribution

All coins excluding #bitcoin have had some sort of "Initial Coin Offering" (ICO).

An unregulated issuance of a security.

The founders and their circle, plus some early adopters, end up with significant (majority) holdings of the token.
Let‚Äôs hope they‚Äôre just washing out the weak hands and we bounce at the bottom of this range #Bitcoin
